Audits and validates Windows SCHANNEL TLS hardening settings by checking protocol status, legacy cipher configuration, and AEAD cipher suite policy enforcement.

Detailed Description

This PowerShell verification script performs a post-hardening assessment of Windows SCHANNEL configuration by:

Reading SCHANNEL protocol settings from the Windows Registry.
Verifying the status of:
SSL 2.0
SSL 3.0
TLS 1.0
TLS 1.1
TLS 1.2
Checking whether legacy cryptographic ciphers remain enabled:
Triple DES (3DES)
RC4 (128-bit and 56-bit variants)
DES
NULL ciphers
Displaying the currently configured cipher suite policy from the Windows Cryptography policy store.
Verifying that AEAD cipher suites (AES-GCM) are present in the configured cipher suite list.
Producing boolean compliance flags for:
TLS 1.0 disabled
TLS 1.1 disabled
TLS 1.2 enabled
SSL 2.0 disabled
SSL 3.0 disabled
3DES disabled
RC4 disabled
DES disabled
NULL ciphers disabled
AEAD cipher suite presence
Generating a human-readable verification report suitable for troubleshooting, auditing, and change validation.




Write-Output "=== TLS AEAD HARDENING VERIFICATION ==="
Write-Output ""

# ---------------------------
# TLS PROTOCOL CHECK
# ---------------------------
$base = "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\SecurityProviders\SCHANNEL\Protocols"

$tls10 = (Get-ItemProperty "$base\TLS 1.0\Server" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled
$tls11 = (Get-ItemProperty "$base\TLS 1.1\Server" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled
$tls12 = (Get-ItemProperty "$base\TLS 1.2\Server" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled

Write-Output "TLS STATUS:"
Write-Output "TLS 1.0 = $tls10"
Write-Output "TLS 1.1 = $tls11"
Write-Output "TLS 1.2 = $tls12"
Write-Output ""

# ---------------------------
# LEGACY PROTOCOL CHECK
# ---------------------------
$ssl2 = (Get-ItemProperty "$base\SSL 2.0\Server" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled
$ssl3 = (Get-ItemProperty "$base\SSL 3.0\Server" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled

Write-Output "LEGACY SSL:"
Write-Output "SSL 2.0 = $ssl2"
Write-Output "SSL 3.0 = $ssl3"
Write-Output ""

# ---------------------------
# LEGACY CIPHER CHECK
# ---------------------------
$cipherBase = "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\SecurityProviders\SCHANNEL\Ciphers"

$tripleDES = (Get-ItemProperty "$cipherBase\Triple DES 168" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled
$rc4_128   = (Get-ItemProperty "$cipherBase\RC4 128/128" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled
$rc4_56    = (Get-ItemProperty "$cipherBase\RC4 56/128" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled
$des56     = (Get-ItemProperty "$cipherBase\DES 56/56" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled
$nullCipher = (Get-ItemProperty "$cipherBase\NULL" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Enabled

Write-Output "LEGACY CIPHERS:"
Write-Output "3DES = $tripleDES"
Write-Output "RC4 128 = $rc4_128"
Write-Output "RC4 56 = $rc4_56"
Write-Output "DES 56 = $des56"
Write-Output "NULL = $nullCipher"
Write-Output ""

# ---------------------------
# AEAD CIPHER SUITE POLICY CHECK
# ---------------------------
$configBase = "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Cryptography\Configuration\SSL\00010002"

$suites = (Get-ItemProperty $configBase -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Functions

Write-Output "CIPHER SUITE POLICY:"
Write-Output $suites
Write-Output ""

# ---------------------------
# SIMPLE VALIDATION OUTPUT (NO BRANCHING)
# ---------------------------
Write-Output "=== HARDENING SUMMARY FLAGS ==="

Write-Output "TLS1.0_DISABLED = $($tls10 -eq 0)"
Write-Output "TLS1.1_DISABLED = $($tls11 -eq 0)"
Write-Output "TLS1.2_ENABLED  = $($tls12 -eq 1)"

Write-Output "SSL2_DISABLED   = $($ssl2 -eq 0)"
Write-Output "SSL3_DISABLED   = $($ssl3 -eq 0)"

Write-Output "3DES_DISABLED   = $($tripleDES -eq 0)"
Write-Output "RC4_DISABLED    = $(($rc4_128 -eq 0) -and ($rc4_56 -eq 0))"
Write-Output "DES_DISABLED    = $($des56 -eq 0)"
Write-Output "NULL_DISABLED   = $($nullCipher -eq 0)"

Write-Output ""

# AEAD detection heuristic (GCM presence)
Write-Output "AEAD_PRESENT = $($suites -match 'GCM')"

Write-Output ""
Write-Output "=== END VERIFICATION ==="
